# automatic paper grading app

a streamlit app that grades arabic exam papers automatically using a vision language model (gemini) and NLP similarity scoring.

## what it does

you upload images of student exam papers, enter the model answers, and the app will:
- extract the student's answers using gemini
- compare them to the model answers
- draw the grades directly on the paper image

supports multiple choice, true/false, and written questions.

## how to use it

1. upload the exam papers (jpg, png, or pdf)
2. enter the number of questions
3. type in the model answer for each question
4. adjust the strictness slider (0 = lenient, 1 = very strict)
5. hit submit and wait for it to grade

make sure all papers have the same questions.

## stack

- streamlit
- google gemini (vision)
- sentence-transformers (paraphrase-multilingual-mpnet-base-v2)
- camel-tools (arabic preprocessing)
- opencv, nltk, rapidfuzz

## setup

add your gemini api key to streamlit secrets:

```
GEMINI_API_KEY = "you can a free one there"
```

get a free key from [aistudio.google.com](https://aistudio.google.com)

